# Rust
/target
**/target
Cargo.lock.bak

# Node / desktop
node_modules/
dist/
.vite/
*.tsbuildinfo
# ...but the desktop shell's dist is a committed placeholder (the window loads the daemon's
# own dashboard, so this page is only a fallback) - keep it tracked.
!/desktop/dist/
!/desktop/dist/index.html
# Tauri build-generated schemas and capability manifests.
/desktop/src-tauri/gen/

# Engram runtime state (local brain - never commit personal memory, the signed ledger, or keys).
# The default ENGRAM_HOME when run from the repo root is ./brain, so ignore the whole home: it
# holds the memory DB, the hash-chained ledger (ledger.jsonl), the public key, and the
# consciousness/workspace state. The earlier db-only globs left ledger.jsonl + consciousness.json
# + workspace.json + ledger.pub committable; ignoring the dir wholesale closes that.
/.engram/
*.engram
/brain/
*.sqlite
*.sqlite-*

# Secrets & env
.env
.env.*
!.env.example
secrets/
*.key
*.pem

# OS / editor
.DS_Store
.idea/
.vscode/*
!.vscode/extensions.json
*.swp

# Logs & temp
*.log
tmp/
.cache/

# Tauri sidecar binaries (copied build artifacts)
/desktop/src-tauri/binaries/

# Local tooling / editor state
.claude/

# Planning & internal design notes — kept local, never published.
